# Deploy Convention

When a deploy is needed, always use `op-firebase-deploy` (global script on PATH).

## Commands

```bash
op-firebase-deploy                  # full deploy (auto-detects project from .firebaserc)
op-firebase-deploy --only hosting   # hosting only
```

## How it works

- `op-firebase-deploy` reads ADC credentials from 1Password (`Private/GCP ADC/credential`)
- Auto-detects the Firebase project from `.firebaserc`
- Writes credentials to a temp file, sets `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`, deploys, cleans up
- No `firebase login`, `gcloud init`, or browser prompts

## Token renewal

The ADC refresh token has no fixed expiry but is revoked on password change, explicit revocation, or 6 months of inactivity. If deploys fail with `invalid_grant` or `Token has been revoked`:

```bash
gcloud auth application-default login --project=swipewatch
op item edit "GCP ADC" --vault Private \
  "credential=$(cat ~/.config/gcloud/application_default_credentials.json)"
```

## Rules

- Never run `firebase deploy` or `npx firebase deploy` directly — always use `op-firebase-deploy`
- Never run `firebase login` or `gcloud auth login` as part of a deploy flow
- Never store or print credentials; only use `op://` references in committed files
